	   <tr><td colspan=2>It is a difficult decision.<br><br>Wizard<br>+Can solo well<br>+Has Gates (travel is very nice and fast)<br>+Can Port (low on money start offering ports)<br>-Not that group friendly (but can travel easy so can try many different places)<br>-dependant on mana (when oom a green will kill you unless you can gate or root it or run away fast enough, remember low hitpoints/ac)<br><br>Rogue<br>+Fairly group friendly<br>+Nice Skills (BS, Poison, Pick Lock, Pick Pocket)<br>+Not Dependant on mana<br>-Hard to Solo (not possible effectively in higher levels)<br>-If can't find group, not easy to travel to another location to check for group<br>-Pays for ports<br>+Can kill low greens easy<br>-If attacked in travel only option is to run, and not many hitpoints so without a SOW you die, higher&nbsp;&nbsp;hitpoints/ac than casters but not near pally, sk, monk, or war. (worse defense of melee types)<br>+Hide/sneak best inv in game<br>-Hide/sneak slowest travel when inv'ed <br><br>Bard<br>+Can really travel fast with drums<br>+Can Solo (via kiting)<br>+Can heal in down time of soloing<br>+Can kill greens with ease <br>+Very Group friendly (can replace an enchanter in some cases)<br>-Not very strong melee wise<br>-Pain in the arse to twist songs<br>-Expected to Twist songs (ie constant workout, caster can take break when medding, melee when casters med or waiting on pull, bards always twisting)<br>-melee damage low and sometimes expected to sit out  to play intrument instead of fight, also may need to mez/charm instead of fight.<br><br>There is my impression of 3 classes with some pros and cons of each, that came to me off the top of my head.<br><br>Splynt <br> <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
